hopobject.body: What sort of work do you do? diphenhydramine dosage webmd I'd still think the Nissan GT-R (about $110,000) is a better buy than this.  The beak grille needs to go.  The last NSX I think sold for a little less than $100,000 and the R8 didn't even exist then, but now, with the Viper GTS, I think the NSX will be a hard sell - especially if it goes beyond $120,000. Unless, this thing goes 0-60 under 3 seconds for about $110,000, it'll just be an ultra low volume halo car.
